1:15:13.291 --> 1:15:16.750
Ma'am, I'm sorry. All offices are closed
today for the Fourth of July picnic.

1:15:17.666 --> 1:15:18.916
That's happening here, right?

1:15:19.000 --> 1:15:20.666
-Yes, ma'am.
-So I can speak to someone now.

1:15:20.750 --> 1:15:22.541
No, ma'am,
there are no appointments today.

1:15:22.625 --> 1:15:26.833
But I wouldn't need an appointment to just
speak to someone at the picnic, right?

1:15:26.916 --> 1:15:29.666
Theoretically, ma'am,
but I can't let you in without a passport.

1:15:30.583 --> 1:15:31.875
Wh-- Just--

1:15:32.500 --> 1:15:33.750
Fine, fine.

1:15:35.458 --> 1:15:37.375
<i>♪ Nothing at all ♪</i>

1:15:38.666 --> 1:15:41.166
<i>♪ And you've got to take it ♪</i>

1:15:43.833 --> 1:15:45.791
<i>♪ From a loser ♪</i>

1:15:45.875 --> 1:15:47.750
<i>♪ From a loser ♪</i>

1:15:47.833 --> 1:15:49.791
<i>♪ Why don't you take it ♪</i>

1:15:49.875 --> 1:15:51.500
What can I get started for you?

1:15:51.583 --> 1:15:53.666
I'll have an Early Times
and soda, please.

1:15:53.750 --> 1:15:58.333
<i>-♪ From a loser ♪</i>
-<i>♪ Take it from someone who knows ♪</i>

1:16:00.416 --> 1:16:03.666
<i>♪ I know how it is to lose that love ♪</i>

1:16:05.541 --> 1:16:06.750
I was just leaving.

1:16:07.916 --> 1:16:08.833
Too late now.

1:16:09.875 --> 1:16:10.958
Is that a last meal?

1:16:13.791 --> 1:16:14.625
Thank you.

1:16:16.666 --> 1:16:18.125
Read any news today?

1:16:20.166 --> 1:16:21.000
Mmm...

1:16:21.916 --> 1:16:26.041
Interesting scoop from a friendly agent
about a woman no one seems to know.

1:16:26.541 --> 1:16:29.750
No record of departing the States,
brief stay at a hotel in San José,

1:16:29.833 --> 1:16:32.916
false passport,
slipped past Antiguan Immigration.

1:16:33.333 --> 1:16:34.291
Fascinating.

1:16:35.791 --> 1:16:38.625
You ready to go on record
with any of that, Mr. Morrison?

1:16:39.000 --> 1:16:39.875
Already have.

1:16:40.375 --> 1:16:42.791
Reporter by the name of Guerrero,
<i>Atlantic Post.</i>

1:16:43.375 --> 1:16:45.000
So you're connected.

1:16:45.541 --> 1:16:48.541
Well, my usual target's been out of touch,
but I hear she's--

1:16:48.625 --> 1:16:51.083
Is it normal for you to be a step behind?

1:16:53.333 --> 1:16:55.625
Wait for someone like me to be in a bind,

1:16:55.708 --> 1:17:00.000
squeeze a bit of distress into the math
so it feels urgent all of a sudden?

1:17:01.000 --> 1:17:03.958
Something you can sink
your well-filed teeth into

1:17:04.041 --> 1:17:06.000
while a secretary forwards your calls?

1:17:06.500 --> 1:17:07.333
Could be.

1:17:08.333 --> 1:17:10.041
But if you had to pick someone
with a byline

1:17:10.125 --> 1:17:11.958
to drop classified intel with,

1:17:12.333 --> 1:17:13.458
wouldn't you pick you?

1:17:13.875 --> 1:17:16.083
Pennsylvania Avenue reporter
with a moral compass

1:17:16.166 --> 1:17:18.291
capable of pointing off the campaign trail

1:17:18.375 --> 1:17:21.166
and delivering a load of munitions
in South America?

1:17:21.250 --> 1:17:22.458
Must be worth reading.

1:17:22.708 --> 1:17:23.625
You think?

1:17:23.916 --> 1:17:26.500
I didn't realize you quasi-spook types
did any reading.

1:17:26.583 --> 1:17:29.041
Not the brightest move,
showing up at the embassy.

1:17:31.083 --> 1:17:34.125
In a perfect world,
we'd make perfect choices.

1:17:34.583 --> 1:17:36.583
In the real world, we make real choices.

1:17:36.666 --> 1:17:38.250
It's not a zero-sum deal.

1:17:38.500 --> 1:17:41.333
Wasn't that your entire thesis
at last year's presentation

1:17:41.416 --> 1:17:43.375
to the Council on Foreign Relations?

1:17:43.666 --> 1:17:44.625
Did you cover that?

1:17:44.708 --> 1:17:48.041
I covered many interesting happenings
before my desk got frozen

1:17:48.125 --> 1:17:50.666
and I was relegated
to following around the circus,

1:17:50.750 --> 1:17:53.500
filing white propaganda
about all the elephant shit.

1:17:53.583 --> 1:17:55.958
Okay. Fair enough.

1:17:57.458 --> 1:17:58.291
Tell you what.

1:17:59.166 --> 1:18:00.041
Let's, uh...

1:18:00.958 --> 1:18:03.666
talk about other interesting happenings.

1:18:04.333 --> 1:18:06.666
<i>♪ From a loser ♪</i>

1:18:08.208 --> 1:18:09.875
<i>Dick McMahon's my father.</i>

1:18:10.958 --> 1:18:15.750
<i>I took his place on a ghost plane</i>
<i>out of Fort Lauderdale on June 29th,</i>

1:18:15.833 --> 1:18:17.291
<i>1:20 in the morning.</i>

1:18:17.875 --> 1:18:19.750
A big-bellied Lockheed

1:18:19.833 --> 1:18:24.625
with enough guns, bullets, mines, and C-4
to take Managua.

1:18:28.541 --> 1:18:30.000
I hustled into the open.

1:18:31.458 --> 1:18:32.333
No payday.

1:18:33.166 --> 1:18:34.875
No protection. No plan.

1:18:35.791 --> 1:18:37.625
Just a game no one let me in on.

1:18:38.375 --> 1:18:39.375
A secret war.

1:18:40.833 --> 1:18:44.166
Now I got a passport with a trick
built into it and no ticket home.

1:18:44.541 --> 1:18:45.541
That I know.

1:18:47.041 --> 1:18:49.166
What I don't know is
why you're still here.

1:18:54.166 --> 1:18:55.375
I came for the money.

1:18:56.250 --> 1:18:57.208
Stayed for the scoop.

1:18:58.000 --> 1:18:58.916
Nice try.

1:19:03.916 --> 1:19:06.125
I came for my father,
stayed for the story.

1:19:08.208 --> 1:19:09.041
Closer.

1:19:13.916 --> 1:19:14.750
All right.

1:19:16.166 --> 1:19:17.583
I don't know why I came.

1:19:20.083 --> 1:19:20.958
But I stayed...

1:19:26.666 --> 1:19:29.666
I... stayed because I was losing focus.

1:19:32.625 --> 1:19:34.375
I can feel it happening again.

1:19:35.000 --> 1:19:35.833
I was...

1:19:35.916 --> 1:19:37.750
I was losing...

1:19:38.625 --> 1:19:41.500
momentum on Catherine, my daughter.

1:19:43.333 --> 1:19:44.750
And I knew that if I...

1:19:47.791 --> 1:19:50.500
walked away from this...

1:19:52.583 --> 1:19:53.750
I would just...

1:19:53.833 --> 1:19:56.708
I would just walk away from everything.
I would just...

1:20:00.458 --> 1:20:01.291
walk away.

1:20:08.833 --> 1:20:10.166
And all I want to know...

1:20:13.916 --> 1:20:15.250
is what you're doing here.

1:20:15.791 --> 1:20:17.458
What you're doing in the picture.

1:20:18.166 --> 1:20:19.000
What...

1:20:20.625 --> 1:20:22.875
if not stirring the pot?

1:20:30.166 --> 1:20:31.666
<i>I thought you were the one.</i>

1:20:35.625 --> 1:20:37.458
I thought you were the one.

1:20:40.750 --> 1:20:43.125
I thought you were the one
they sent to kill me.

1:20:45.458 --> 1:20:46.416
I was ready.

1:20:53.208 --> 1:20:54.791
Diane had a scar like this.

1:20:57.875 --> 1:20:59.750
Then she just went.

1:21:02.916 --> 1:21:05.333
"The seal's wide spindrift gaze..."

1:21:07.250 --> 1:21:08.250
Something,

1:21:09.458 --> 1:21:11.791
"Galleons of Carib fire..."

1:21:11.875 --> 1:21:13.125
Something, something.

1:21:13.583 --> 1:21:18.750
"The seal's wide spindrift gaze
towards paradise."

1:21:20.625 --> 1:21:21.916
Diane loved poetry.

1:21:23.833 --> 1:21:25.250
Alcestis.

1:21:26.291 --> 1:21:28.708
Back from the tunnel
and half in love with death.

1:21:32.250 --> 1:21:33.125
Tomorrow.

1:21:39.375 --> 1:21:40.333
Tomorrow what?

1:21:41.833 --> 1:21:42.875
Tomorrow we leave.

1:21:54.083 --> 1:21:55.916
- Come on. Give me this.
- What? No.

1:21:56.000 --> 1:21:58.375
- This is the second time.
- Can you give it back?

1:21:58.458 --> 1:21:59.583
No. Come on.

1:21:59.666 --> 1:22:00.541
-Yes.
-No.

1:22:00.625 --> 1:22:02.541
-No.
-Listen, you can't sell here. No.

1:22:02.625 --> 1:22:05.416
- Can I sell this?
- No, you can't sell this. No.

1:22:05.708 --> 1:22:09.291
-Chalatenango. Unbelievable.
-This is the second time.

1:22:09.375 --> 1:22:11.833
Shit, at least when you drive a stake
through a vampire's heart,

1:22:11.916 --> 1:22:13.500
-the fucker dies.
-Hey.

1:22:15.833 --> 1:22:16.708
See you tomorrow.

1:22:17.041 --> 1:22:18.958
- Good time, man
- Yeah, man.

1:22:19.041 --> 1:22:21.000
- Have a good night.
- Catch you later.

1:22:21.083 --> 1:22:21.958
Coming in tomorrow?

1:22:22.666 --> 1:22:24.458
-No.
-Give it back to me!

1:22:24.833 --> 1:22:25.833
Hey.

1:22:32.500 --> 1:22:34.208
-Elena!

1:22:55.583 --> 1:22:57.500
<i>Guests, please stay in your rooms...</i>

1:23:18.625 --> 1:23:21.875
Your countrymen aren't your countrymen.
There's no reason you should be here.

1:23:21.958 --> 1:23:24.958
But you can't tell me who you are
or how you know any of this.

1:23:25.041 --> 1:23:27.833
I think they just spelled the story out
in bullets, yes?

1:23:42.333 --> 1:23:44.833
Through there! Through there!
Make we pass!

1:23:44.916 --> 1:23:46.333
Make we pass!

1:23:47.083 --> 1:23:48.458
Hey, make we pass, brethren!

1:23:48.541 --> 1:23:50.416
Hey, make we pass, through there!

1:24:22.166 --> 1:24:23.291
Don't you see?

1:24:23.458 --> 1:24:26.250
They had to give your father
a figure big enough to lure him out.

1:24:26.958 --> 1:24:29.291
A magical million-dollar payday.

1:24:30.083 --> 1:24:31.750
He's a half-crazy old man
in a sick season.

1:24:31.833 --> 1:24:33.750
-My father is not--
- He's a man

1:24:33.833 --> 1:24:36.083
with a well-documented history

1:24:36.166 --> 1:24:38.958
of not caring
where his merchandise showed up.

1:24:39.833 --> 1:24:41.958
And so, he's a man very easily placed

1:24:42.041 --> 1:24:44.375
on the wrong side
of whatever was supposed to happen.

1:24:45.458 --> 1:24:47.125
"Gunrunner bleeds out in...

1:24:47.208 --> 1:24:49.333
in-- in terrorist attack
at Caribbean resort."

1:24:49.416 --> 1:24:50.250
So what?

1:24:50.875 --> 1:24:51.833
Who would miss him?

1:24:52.791 --> 1:24:53.666
Who would care?

1:24:54.833 --> 1:24:55.666
You?

1:24:57.791 --> 1:24:58.833
File closed.

1:24:59.791 --> 1:25:01.625
Finished and done.

1:25:03.541 --> 1:25:05.125
But you...

1:25:06.250 --> 1:25:07.416
You, Elena...

1:25:08.041 --> 1:25:09.375
But you showed up instead.

1:25:10.166 --> 1:25:12.708
And the file is still closing.

1:25:13.583 --> 1:25:17.958
All the little scraps and pieces
being assembled for the archive,

1:25:18.041 --> 1:25:19.125
to be forgotten.

1:25:19.583 --> 1:25:21.250
And yours is the last name on it.

1:25:21.333 --> 1:25:22.541
The passport, it--

1:25:22.625 --> 1:25:26.375
The only trick of the passport
was to keep you in play.

1:25:26.458 --> 1:25:29.250
You could have got on a plane
and left this place.

1:25:29.333 --> 1:25:32.041
No, the passport wouldn't be valid
for re-entry to the US,

1:25:32.125 --> 1:25:34.000
at which point you would have been taken.

1:25:34.083 --> 1:25:38.250
Rescued, rather, by the authorities,
which gave you more of a reason to leave.

1:25:39.875 --> 1:25:40.833
But no.

1:25:41.708 --> 1:25:43.416
You... you're still here.

1:25:46.750 --> 1:25:48.958
All I have left is this story, I admit it.

1:26:00.750 --> 1:26:01.666
Do you know who...

1:26:03.291 --> 1:26:05.291
the unreported casualties of...

1:26:06.000 --> 1:26:06.916
of Vietnam were?

1:26:10.333 --> 1:26:11.333
The reporters...

1:26:12.875 --> 1:26:14.208
who couldn't move past it.

1:26:17.625 --> 1:26:18.666
Hey, Jones.

1:26:18.750 --> 1:26:19.708
All clear.

1:26:23.791 --> 1:26:26.000
You can stay here.
There's a phone across the square.

1:26:26.500 --> 1:26:27.708
One day, maybe two.

1:26:28.375 --> 1:26:30.750
I'll talk with my comrades
on getting us a boat.

1:26:32.666 --> 1:26:34.333
We are meant to survive
beyond our stories.

1:27:40.000 --> 1:27:40.833
Guerrero speaking.

1:27:41.291 --> 1:27:42.541
-It's me.
- <i>Elena?</i>

1:27:42.625 --> 1:27:44.416
Call Catherine's father. Call Wynn.

1:27:44.750 --> 1:27:46.541
When you hang up with me, call him.

1:27:46.625 --> 1:27:48.958
Tell him to go to Catherine's school.
Tell him to go get her.

1:27:49.041 --> 1:27:52.625
Tell him not to send anybody.
Tell him he's gotta go himself, in person.

1:27:52.708 --> 1:27:55.375
And tell him I need him to keep her,
just until I get back.

1:27:55.458 --> 1:27:56.750
Done. Ellie...

1:27:58.291 --> 1:27:59.125
Dick is dead.

1:28:02.625 --> 1:28:03.458
I know.

1:28:03.541 --> 1:28:05.500
<i>They moved him</i>
<i>the night after you left.</i>

1:28:05.583 --> 1:28:07.041
<i>The hospital wouldn't let me see him.</i>

1:28:07.125 --> 1:28:09.083
<i>And then I wasn't sure</i>
<i>if I should reach you</i>

1:28:09.166 --> 1:28:11.291
<i>or if reaching you</i>
<i>would expose you, but...</i>

1:28:11.375 --> 1:28:12.708
I'm sorry, Elena.

1:28:12.791 --> 1:28:13.625
But listen.

1:28:15.291 --> 1:28:19.291
My sources are telling me that there is
a French intelligence operative down there

1:28:19.375 --> 1:28:21.208
investigating the same thing that we are.

1:28:21.291 --> 1:28:23.000
<i>Okay? I don't have a name yet,</i>

1:28:23.083 --> 1:28:26.583
<i>but they could get you a special visa</i>
<i>and get you out of there.</i>

1:28:26.666 --> 1:28:29.083
These people
are starting to move faster.

1:28:29.875 --> 1:28:31.750
The InterCon assassination attempt...

1:28:33.500 --> 1:28:34.916
-I was there.
- <i>I know.</i>

1:28:35.000 --> 1:28:38.541
I know. Look, we're all over it down here.
But you should be safe for now.

1:28:38.958 --> 1:28:40.625
<i>They're beefing up the military presence.</i>

1:28:40.708 --> 1:28:43.375
No, the military was already there
in full force before the attempt.

1:28:43.458 --> 1:28:44.708
They knew it was coming.

1:28:45.125 --> 1:28:46.541
And I was meant to be there.

1:28:47.208 --> 1:28:49.125
Two birds, one stone. The file closes.

1:28:49.208 --> 1:28:50.041
<i>What?</i>

1:28:50.375 --> 1:28:52.750
The date on my bogus passport's
the same day Dick died.

1:28:52.833 --> 1:28:53.833
<i>Okay, calm down.</i>

1:28:54.541 --> 1:28:57.125
<i>Listen. Just stay where you are for now.</i>

1:28:57.208 --> 1:28:59.916
"Gunrunner bleeds out
in terrorist attack."

1:29:00.000 --> 1:29:01.583
You showed up instead.

1:29:03.166 --> 1:29:04.875
<i>Hello?</i> <i>Elena?</i>

1:29:07.000 --> 1:29:08.208
<i>Elena? Hello?</i>

1:29:08.291 --> 1:29:09.125
Elena!

1:29:10.541 --> 1:29:11.375
Elena!

1:29:16.416 --> 1:29:17.250
Elena!

1:29:29.000 --> 1:29:31.500
There are two things
I need you to know right away.

1:29:35.083 --> 1:29:39.208
The first thing I need you to know
is that you get to go back to Malibu.

1:29:40.000 --> 1:29:41.666
<i>Your dad's coming to pick you up.</i>

1:29:43.041 --> 1:29:45.875
<i>Do not go with anyone except your dad.</i>
<i>Do you understand?</i>

1:29:48.250 --> 1:29:50.250
<i>The second thing I need you to know...</i>

1:29:51.500 --> 1:29:52.750
<i>is that I love you.</i>

1:29:54.625 --> 1:29:56.166
<i>Sometimes... </i>

1:29:56.250 --> 1:29:59.083
<i>we argue and... about things, but I...</i>

1:30:01.250 --> 1:30:02.916
<i>I think you know...</i>

1:30:03.750 --> 1:30:07.208
<i>I only argue because</i>
<i>I want your life to be happy and good.</i>

1:30:08.416 --> 1:30:10.416
<i>Want you not to waste your time.</i>

1:30:11.291 --> 1:30:12.708
<i>Not to waste your talent.</i>

1:30:14.416 --> 1:30:17.375
<i>Not to let who you are get mixed up</i>

1:30:17.458 --> 1:30:19.916
<i>with anyone else's idea</i>
<i>of who you should be.</i>

1:30:21.750 --> 1:30:23.083
<i>I know you're nodding.</i>

1:30:25.708 --> 1:30:27.958
<i>I love you the most. You're my Kit-Cat.</i>

1:30:36.541 --> 1:30:37.708
Okay.

1:30:38.125 --> 1:30:40.083
Everything's set. A car will take you.

1:30:40.375 --> 1:30:41.333
His name is Paul.

1:30:41.416 --> 1:30:42.458
<i>He's expecting you.</i>

1:30:43.125 --> 1:30:46.333
<i>No one will look for you there.</i>
<i>Now, I've been working with the consulate.</i>

1:30:46.416 --> 1:30:48.166
<i>We're gonna extract you</i>
<i>in the next few days. </i>

1:30:48.250 --> 1:30:51.416
<i>If anything happens, don't come to me.</i>
<i>It's too dangerous for you here.</i>

1:30:51.958 --> 1:30:53.625
<i>I'll come to you. Okay?</i>

1:30:56.208 --> 1:30:57.125
Can I help you?

1:30:57.666 --> 1:30:58.500
Hi.

1:30:58.875 --> 1:31:00.250
Uh, I'm Elise.

1:31:00.333 --> 1:31:01.250
Elise Meyer.

1:31:02.458 --> 1:31:05.375
Highly recommended Elise Meyer of Miami?

1:31:06.375 --> 1:31:08.708
Get up here.
Let's get you started already.

1:31:10.166 --> 1:31:13.625
Who wants to be sitting around
a bunch of jarheaded machos downtown

1:31:13.708 --> 1:31:16.166
when you can live
right on the edge of paradise?

1:31:16.750 --> 1:31:19.666
So, this job is not complicated at all.

1:31:20.416 --> 1:31:22.625
Each day, 10:00 a.m. sharp,

1:31:23.250 --> 1:31:24.250
routinely,

1:31:24.833 --> 1:31:27.791
pick us up fruit from the vendor
at Heritage Market.

1:31:28.000 --> 1:31:29.291
I can get it from closer.

1:31:29.375 --> 1:31:31.625
No, Heritage Market. Thank you.

1:31:31.916 --> 1:31:34.000
Guavas from the stall near the entrance.

1:31:34.458 --> 1:31:37.750
Uh, pick us up newspapers
from the little woman two streets over.

1:31:37.833 --> 1:31:40.500
And get all the newspapers.
I like to be well-read.

1:31:41.041 --> 1:31:44.458
Plus, when guests come,
we want to be prepared.

1:31:45.166 --> 1:31:47.000
And, uh, let me see.

1:31:48.041 --> 1:31:49.083
We have a cook,

1:31:49.750 --> 1:31:50.583
Evelina,

1:31:50.666 --> 1:31:53.000
who comes every day at five
and handles supper,

1:31:53.083 --> 1:31:54.583
so you don't need to worry about that.

1:31:54.666 --> 1:31:55.750
But just, you know...

1:31:57.125 --> 1:31:58.208
tidy things.

1:32:00.125 --> 1:32:01.333
I could wipe the chairs.

1:32:02.791 --> 1:32:04.041
They said you were sharp.

1:32:05.000 --> 1:32:08.666
<i>♪ I ain't never seen a man ♪</i>

